p.q:
That the Clergy are not Lords and Profeſſors of Tythes and other Eccleſiaſtical Goods, which are freely given, but only Stewards;Acts & Mon. pag. 605.
                      and after the neceſſity of the Clergy is once ſatisfied, they ought to be tranſported to the poor; and if the Clergy do abuſe the ſame, they are Thieves and Robbers, and Sacriledgious perſons;

& except they do Repent by the Judgment of God they are to be condemned.
